        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 6:23PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 623 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of North La Junta, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Las Animas and John Martin Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
